<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2016/12/06/springone-platform-2016-replay-going-reactive-building-better-microservices">SpringOne Platform 2016 Replay: Going Reactive: Building Better Microservices</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2016-12-06 04:56:00.0">December 6, 2016</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2725" href="/blog/2016/12/06/springone-platform-2016-replay-going-reactive-building-better-microservices#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne Platform 2016.<br>Speaker: Rob Harrop, Skipjaq<br>Slides: <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/going-reactive-building-better-microservices-rob-harrop">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/going-reactive-building-better-microservices-rob-harrop</a></p>
<p>Reactive provides developers with an elegant model for constructing applications out of communicating components that improves code readability, eases concurrent programming and supports fine-grained unit testing.</p>
<p>In this talk, we’ll see how this model is a natural fit for building resilient microservices. Specifically, we’ll see how to:</p>
</div>
</section>
